comment.body: Happy New Year to you too Nofish!

> [gitcenter](#comment_1_1Cy3ntkN2GN9MH6EaW6eHpi4YoRS2nK5Di): Both work, first letter case does not matter (though it's most likely a typo)

This does matter. The python implementation may not care about the command's case, but a protocol should be clearly defined. My Rust implementation of ZeroNet is case-sensitive (using camelCase, not PascalCase) so I've had to add an additional case just to deal with the malformed "FilterIncludeList" command.
